 Datatypes in PL/SQL :- 
 ==================

   1  scalar types or built-in types 
   2  user define types 
   3  reference types 

  scalar types / built-in types :-
  -----------------------------------------

    1   NUMBER(P) / NUMBER(P,S)
    2   CHAR / VARCHAR2 / LONG / CLOB
    3   NCHAR/NVARCHAR2/NCLOB
    4   DATE / TIMESTAMP 
    5   BOOLEAN   
    6   BFILE / BLOB
    7   BINARY_FLOAT / BINARY_DOUBLE
    8   BINARY_INTEGER
  
      1 TO 7   => allowed in  sql,pl/sql
      8            => allowed only in pl/sql but not allowed in sql 
  
